subSubSection.paragraph:
LEGS (
Fig. 9A
). Legs predominantly shiny black except for brownish-orange apex of femora, basal narrow orange margin of tibiae and orange tarsomeres ventrally; short whitish pilose; mesotrochanter weakly pollinose and with pile ventrally; metatarsus with a short tuft of orange pile ventrally; metafemur simple, slightly enlarged, about 3.75 times as long as wide, ventral pile very short and about 1/6–1/7 of width of metafemur; anteroventral and posteroventral margins of metafemur each with a row of 10 respectively 7 black setae apically.

ABDOMEN. Predominantly reddish-brown; tergum I black with whitish pile laterally; terga II–IV reddishbrown, white pilose, each with a pair of oblique maculae of white pollinosity; tergum II with a median black ‛pewter chalice’-shaped vitta; tergum III with a median longitudinal black vitta on anterior half; sterna reddish-brown, yellowish pilose; sternum IV almost square, with median V-shaped incision posteriorly (
Fig. 12A
).
